article.headline: Duquesne 96, Ohio 91
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Jon Pawlak had 15 points as Duquesne made better than two-thirds of its shots to withstand 20 3-pointers by Ohio for a 96-91 victory Wednesday night. Trailing 5-2 with 18:41 in the first half, Duquesne (5-7) went on an 11-0 run and never trailed again. The Dukes led 42-28 at the half and led by as many as many as 22 points. The Dukes shot 66.7 percent (34-51) from the field -- the first time they shot better than 60 percent from the field since 1993 -- to hold off a record-setting 3-point shooting performance by the Bobcats. The Bobcats (3-9) made 20 of 44 shots from 3-point range -- a record for 3-point shots made at the Palumbo Center. Thomas Stephens led all scorers with 28 points, including six 3-pointers, while Jaivon Harris had 22 points and also made six shots from 3-point range for the Bobcats. Jeff Halbert added 13 points for Ohio. Elijah Palmer and Ron Dokes had 14 points each, while Bryant McAllister added 12 points and Ryan Tricco had 10 points for the Dukes.
